## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="24c57-118">下面的示例演示的处理程序`SpeechRecognized`事件<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>或<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer>对象，以及有关关联的信息的一些<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24c57-118">The following example shows a handler for the `SpeechRecognized` event of a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> object, and some of the information about the associated <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
// Handle the SpeechRecognized event.   
void SpeechRecognizedHandler(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
{  
  if (e.Result == null) return;  
  
  // Add event handler code here.  
  
  // The following code illustrates some of the information available  
  // in the recognition result.  
  Console.WriteLine("Grammar({0}), {1}: {2}",  
    e.Result.Grammar.Name, e.Result.Audio.Duration, e.Result.Text);  
  
  // Display the semantic values in the recognition result.  
  foreach (KeyValuePair<String, SemanticValue> child in e.Result.Semantics)  
  {  
    Console.WriteLine(" {0} key: {1}",  
      child.Key, child.Value.Value ?? "null");  
  }  
  Console.WriteLine();  
  
  // Display information about the words in the recognition result.  
  foreach (RecognizedWordUnit word in e.Result.Words)  
  {  
    RecognizedAudio audio = e.Result.GetAudioForWordRange(word, word);  
    Console.WriteLine(" {0,-10} {1,-10} {2,-10} {3} ({4})",  
      word.Text, word.LexicalForm, word.Pronunciation,  
      audio.Duration, word.DisplayAttributes);  
  }  
  
  // Display the recognition alternates for the result.  
  foreach (RecognizedPhrase phrase in e.Result.Alternates)  
  {  
    Console.WriteLine(" alt({0}) {1}", phrase.Confidence, phrase.Text);  
  }  
}  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="24c57-121">识别<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A>排序的值及其<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A>属性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24c57-121">Recognition <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A> are ordered by the values of their <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A> properties.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="24c57-122">给定的短语的置信度值指示短语的输入匹配的概率。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24c57-122">The confidence value of a given phrase indicates the probability that the phrase matches the input.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="24c57-123">使用最高置信度值短语是最有可能的输入匹配的短语。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24c57-123">The phrase with the highest confidence value is the phrase that most likely matches the input.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="24c57-124">每个<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A>单独和无需对其他的置信度值引用还应评估价值<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24c57-124">Each <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A> value should be evaluated individually and without reference to the confidence values of other <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="24c57-125">属性的<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>继承自<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>短语有关的详细的信息提供最高置信度得分。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24c57-125">The properties that the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult> inherits from <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> provide detailed information about the phrase with the highest confidence score.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="24c57-126">一个用于<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A>集合是为自动的错误更正。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24c57-126">One use for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A> collection is for automated error correction.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="24c57-127">例如，在设计目录对话框时，应用程序可能提示用户以检查是否应用程序中，从识别事件，正确的信息"，您是否 Anna？"如果用户显示"否"，则应用程序无法查询有关任何备用项具有足够高的用户<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A>分数。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24c57-127">For example, when designing a directory dialog, an application could prompt the user to check if the application has the correct information from a recognition event, as in, "Did you say 'Anna'?" If the user says "no", then the application could query the user about any alternates that had a high enough <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A> score.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="24c57-128">有关语音识别和使用情况将识别备用项的详细信息，请参阅[语音识别](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/6a7dc524-07fc-4862-8d48-8c10dc64b919)和[使用语音识别事件](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/01c598ca-2e0e-4e89-b303-cd1cef9e8482)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="24c57-128">For more information about speech recognition and the use of recognition alternates, see [Speech Recognition](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/6a7dc524-07fc-4862-8d48-8c10dc64b919) and [Using Speech Recognition Events](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/01c598ca-2e0e-4e89-b303-cd1cef9e8482).</span></span>  
  
   
  
